import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data.boxplot(column='total', by='region')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of income across different regions?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
    ax.set_ylabel('Total Income')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.suptitle('')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_income_pct = data.groupby('region')['pct'].mean()
    avg_income_pct.plot(kind='bar', rot=0)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the average income percentage for each region?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.scatter(data['pct'], data['group'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the relationship between income percentage and income group?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    income_group_by_region = data.groupby(['region', 'group']).size().unstack()
    income_group_by_region.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of income groups across different regions?")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
